oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Engraving of George Clinton (1739-1812), posed in Revolutionary War uniform, leaning against cannon with musket nearby. In the background are mountains, trees, and the sky.
Governor of New York, 1777-1795, 1801-1804; Brigadier General, Continental Army; U.S. Vice President under Jefferson and Madison.
